font-size:11pt">pre-booking ahead cannot be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">guaranteed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> where </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">routeing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">compromise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">take account of all users across an area. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.3. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Engagement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with young people </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">suggest</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tend</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> not to favour </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pre-booked DRT services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">they</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> feel </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">better served by regular timetabled services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">given the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">“turn-up-and-go”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> nature of much of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> their travel patterns.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Fare levels can also be a barrier for young people’s travel.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What are the main challenges associated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is difficult to generalise on specific solutions g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">iven geographical differences across the country in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">both urban and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rural areas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> where isolation is an issue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> terrain, road pattern</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">/ density</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, the various ways different towns can act as a draw for people to visit and work, etc.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Barriers to travel can occur in urban as well as rural areas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.2. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A one size-fits all approach </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in relation to service type is unlikely to be beneficially applied to all rural </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or urban </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">areas. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Different </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> types, and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">different</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> mixes at times of DRT and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">timetable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, will suit different areas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.3. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Rural </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">passenger </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">flows are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">frequently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">diverse and often cannot easily be aggregated together into cost-efficient routes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Where there are different needs - in different directions, at different times, or at interchanges onto or from a train service – </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">it is has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be a pre-requisite of public tr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ansport planning that priority </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tends to focus on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> “the greatest benefit for the greatest number” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> needs that can be met cost-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">effectiv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Inevitably</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> therefore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">other needs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> not be met</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> - </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ural transport cannot </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">always </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be all things to all people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in an </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> many people </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> feel that it serves their needs badly if at all, even if the predominant needs are catered for.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ural employment is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">often </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">characterised by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">many </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mall &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">edium </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nterprises (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">SMEs) in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">widely scattered </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">locations. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Significant and established flows </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to work </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are therefore often difficult to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">provide for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengers in isolated communities? How could Community Transport be improved?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Community transport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(CT) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">often primarily</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> focus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on the needs of the frail elderly and disabled</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and less well on the needs of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">people who need transport to get to work, or the travel needs of young people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.2. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The sector is very diverse, from some larg</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">er community transport groups that act virtually as commercial operators in tendering for large contracts, through to many small groups, often with just one or two vehicles, for whom the Community Interest Company model </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> seen to be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> both less beneficial and less relevant. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.3. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The difficulties </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in serving </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">isolated areas are the same for community transport as for commercial operators and councils: serv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ices </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">will always </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tend to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">require significant subsidy to meet the shortfall between</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> operating costs and fares revenue from relatively small numbers of passengers travelling. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.4. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Community</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">transport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> best serves i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s own community: m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">any rural council funded bus routes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unsuitable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for CT operation as they serve </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a number of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">communities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> across rel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">v</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">long di</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ta</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ces</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Other b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">arriers to CT operation of these services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may include</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the need for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">premises and operating centres </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">large </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">buses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> needed for many current </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">routes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is li</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ke</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ly to be a major deterrent to many commu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nity groups</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">limits</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to volunteering efforts and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to fund-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">raise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for high cost </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">; will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">volunteer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-based</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> organisations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ant to expect volunteers to work </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unpaid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">convey </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">passengers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to paid employment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Lic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ns</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ng const</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ra</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ints; the recent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">extension to Section 19 provisions exclude paid drivers for certain vehicles.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.5. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The view</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that community tra</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sport will simply back-fill </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bus </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">servi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">es cut by councils</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is unlikely to become a reality. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Most services for isolated rural areas that are council funded are likely to continue to require revenue support; that is why they are supported and not commercial in the first place. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">injection</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of kickstart </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">funding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is unlikely to provide lasting long-t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">erm </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">improved </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">viability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">felt to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">generally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of limited value, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">certain circumstances only, such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">services that are relatively close to financial sustainab</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and just need a push to achieve viability.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.6. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">here are clearly exceptions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">where </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">geography etc. may help</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> enable a more viable operation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, but on the whole there is little scope for making services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">serving </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">isolated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">communities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, or even many rural</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">areas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">generally</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sustainable. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We need therefore to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">understand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that it is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unrealistic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o suppose that:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(i) if only </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supported</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> were managed or operated in a different way they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">would</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> not need support;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(ii) council funded bus services will be routinely operated by the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">community</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">transport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sector</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> if the council </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">funding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ends. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Taxis are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">seen as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">universally available, but the cost is clearly prohibitive for regular use for many people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">heelchair accessible taxis are not universally available in rural areas. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Joseph Rowntree Foundation (2010) identified that Transport Poverty is a greater factor in rural areas than Fuel Poverty</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, but we still hear more about the latter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.2. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">RT s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">er</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">vices are often unsuitable for regular commuting to work. Often schemes only allow for booking up to a week/ fortnight ahead, which in itself is a barrier to meeting workers’ travel needs.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DRT can be seen to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">provide</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> better</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for off-peak accessibility needs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to shopping/ town centre facilities and services.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.3. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DRT often has higher costs per passenger than conventional bus services. A number of DRT services promoted as a cost-effective way to provide access in rural areas have in recent years been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">terminated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> due to high costs.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It cannot therefore be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">assumed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that there is a continuum of reducing service levels in line with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reducing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> cost </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">per </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">passenger</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">),</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">high frequency buses to low frequency buses to DRT: when replacing low frequency buses with DRT costs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">er passenger</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">frequently</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> found to rise. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.4. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The cost of o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ff</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">peak rural services i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s often lower by using</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> resources more fully, i.e. using buses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> -</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on the margin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> - </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that are fully used in the peak for commuting etc., </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as opposed to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">less efficient use of resources such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">se buses being parked </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">up </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in the off-peak and using other smaller vehicles for off-peak DRT services.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities? How can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">these services be made more affordable?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Many public transport services serving isolated communities can never become sustainable, given the low revenue compared to costs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the aspiration to make these services affordable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in terms of financial viability </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may be largely unobtainable. The degree to which the level of financial support needed can be seen to be acceptable is determined by a number of factors. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">.2. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ENCTS</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The continued high cost of the ENCTS public transport spe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nd acts as a barrier to continuing spend on supporting rural public transport services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Given the pressure on budgets</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> many councils </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">understandably feel they are already spending too much on public transport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">.3. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Cross-sector </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Benefits</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline"> and Challenges</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">For most councils their funding of bus services is probably the greatest single positive impact (compared to any other initiative) on each of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the following key policy aims</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Equality</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of opportunity - regardless of where someone lives or whether they can drive/ have a car</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Reducing barriers to employment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> – for current workers and job-seekers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The economy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">connectivity with skills and the reliance of retail businesses on bus passengers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Y</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">outh opportunities</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Sustainable communities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> - where people are independent and self-reliant</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Health Improvement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">access to health, active travel and the ability to have a healthy lifestyle)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">independent living, reduced dependency on benefits and individual c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are services; the Prevention Agenda</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.4. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Whilst t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">his is felt to be often generally unrecognised across councils and central government</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, If the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">se</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> cross sector benefits could be levered into funding services, these services are likely in many cases to become affordable.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.5. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The cross-sector benefits of bus services are significant. This has been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">recently evidenced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in many national reports from a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> wide range of bodies (Appendix 1) and yet continues to be largely unrecognised</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in government policies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A significant element of th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">value of bus services lies in other organisations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e.g.:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The NHS: access to healthcare</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (often becoming more remote as health services are reconfigured) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for those without a car; health improvement through healthy and active lifestyles within those without a car can only enjoy trough convenient and affordable public transport;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DWP/ Jobcentre+</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">: through enabling job-seekers to get to work who would otherwise remain on benefit.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">However with services under pressure and the need for short term cost reductions, there </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">appears to be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> little incentive to consider longer term benefits from working </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">across organisations. It also requires </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">these other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">agencies to decide to spend money other than within their areas of professional expertise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> by diverting funding to transport. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> absence of central polic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">es</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on these lines</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ouncils have a pivotal, but culturally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">very </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">difficult, role to play in facilitating this if the best long-term decisions are to be made.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">felt to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">not c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">onstructive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for government to leave these decisions to local government when </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> financ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">es are being </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reduced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to such an extent that non-statutory services, no matter how worthy or recognised those services may be within a council, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">provide the main scope for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">cut</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to meet the budget reductions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">et by central government</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> under the Spending Review</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 2.15pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-si